    "body": "I really don't want to have to specify full paths for cimports if I can avoid it.....\r\n\r\nWithin a package, this is valid in python with normal import, but not in Cython with cimport (in python 2.7 with language level='3'):\r\n```\r\ncimport .common_scroll_geo as comm\r\n```\r\nand you must do\r\n```\r\ncimport PDSim.common_scroll_geo as comm\r\n```\r\nand the error received is quite obtuse:\r\n```\r\nError compiling Cython file:\r\n------------------------------------------------------------\r\n...\r\nimport numpy as np\r\nimport cython\r\n\r\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\r\n\r\ncimport .common_scroll_geo as comm\r\n       ^\r\n------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nPDSim/scroll/symm_scroll_geo.pyx:8:8: Expected an identifier\r\n```\r\n",
